     {q:"Canadian women gained the right to vote in federal elections in which year?", options:["1918","1867","1950","1982"], answer:0},
     {q:"The timeline for women gaining the right to vote in Canada ___.", options:["Never actually changed over time","Was identical for every woman in Canada with no variation","Varied for different groups of women","Has no connection to Canadian history"], answer:2},
     {q:"Why is the women’s suffrage movement considered a significant part of Canadian history?", options:["This movement never actually took place","It had no lasting impact on Canadian society","It represented a major step toward expanding political rights and equality","It occurred with no organized advocacy involved"], answer:2},
     {q:"Why might historians note that suffrage timelines varied among different groups of Canadian women?", options:["Suffrage was never a contested or gradual process","All Canadian women gained the right to vote on the exact same day","Not all women gained voting rights at the same time due to differing laws and barriers","This variation has no historical significance"], answer:2}
