     {q:"Blending as a word formation process involves ___.", options:["Removing all vowels from a word","Using only whole, unaltered words","Combining parts of two words into a new word, like brunch from breakfast and lunch","A process unrelated to vocabulary"], answer:2},
     {q:"Why is understanding etymology useful when encountering unfamiliar words?", options:["Word origins never provide any useful clues","Recognizing familiar roots can help readers infer meaning","Etymology has no connection to understanding word meaning","Etymology only applies to very short words"], answer:1},
     {q:"Which is an example of a blended word?", options:["Notebook","Sunflower","Smog (from smoke and fog)","Basketball"], answer:2}
