     {q:"If a sphere has a radius of 3 units, which expression represents its volume?", options:["Pi times 3 squared","Four-thirds pi times 3 cubed","One-third pi times 3 squared","Two pi times 3"], answer:1},
     {q:"Why might understanding the volume of cones and spheres be useful in real-world design?", options:["These shapes never appear in real-world objects","Cones and spheres have no measurable volume","Volume calculations have no practical design applications","Many real objects, like ice cream cones or balls, are based on these shapes"], answer:3}
