     {q:"In a Venn diagram, the overlapping region between two circles represents ___.", options:["A concept unrelated to Venn diagrams","Elements belonging to neither set","The intersection of the two sets","The union of the two sets"], answer:2},
     {q:"Why are Venn diagrams useful when calculating probabilities involving multiple events?", options:["They help visualize which outcomes belong to one, both, or neither event","A reason unrelated to probability","They can only be used with a single event at a time","Venn diagrams provide no useful information for probability"], answer:0}
