     {q:"Why is the Multiculturalism Act often referenced when discussing Canadian identity?", options:["It has no connection to how Canadian identity is understood","It formally rejected the idea of a diverse Canadian society","A reason unrelated to its historical significance","It reflects an official commitment to embracing cultural diversity as part of being Canadian"], answer:3}
