     {q:"Unit pricing calculates ___.", options:["A concept unrelated to unit pricing","The cost per single unit of an item","The total cost of an entire package regardless of size","The tax applied to a purchase"], answer:1},
     {q:"If 1 CAD = 0.75 USD, how many USD would you receive for 200 CAD?", options:["200 USD","150 USD","266.67 USD","A value unrelated to the calculation"], answer:1},
     {q:"A 500 g box of cereal costs 5 dollars, and a 750 g box costs 6 dollars. Which has the lower unit price per gram?", options:["A result unrelated to the calculation","The 750 g box","They have exactly the same unit price","The 500 g box"], answer:1},
     {q:"Why is unit pricing useful for consumers when shopping?", options:["It allows a fair comparison of value between differently sized packages","Larger packages are always the better value regardless of price","A reason unrelated to unit pricing","Unit pricing provides no useful information for comparing products"], answer:0}
