     {q:"Pier 21 served as a major immigration gateway to Canada between ___.", options:["1867 and 1900","1928 and 1971","A time period unrelated to Pier 21","1980 and 2000"], answer:1},
     {q:"Many newcomers who arrived through Pier 21 after the Second World War were ___.", options:["Refugees and immigrants seeking a new life in Canada","A group unrelated to Pier 21","Government officials with no connection to immigration","Exclusively tourists visiting for a short stay"], answer:0},
     {q:"Pier 21 is significant in Canadian history because it ___.", options:["Welcomed hundreds of thousands of immigrants, shaping Canada’s post-war population","Prevented any immigration to Canada during this period","Was used only for exporting goods, with no connection to immigration","A reason unrelated to its historical significance"], answer:0},
     {q:"Why is Pier 21 today commemorated as a national museum?", options:["To preserve the history and stories of the immigrants who passed through it","Because it has no connection to Canadian immigration history","To celebrate a location with no historical importance to Canada","A reason unrelated to Pier 21"], answer:0}
