     {q:"Are bioplastics considered an alternative to traditional plastics made from petroleum?", options:["No, bioplastics have no connection to traditional plastics","Bioplastics are exactly the same as petroleum-based plastics","Yes","A concept unrelated to bioplastics"], answer:2},
     {q:"Name one renewable source that can be used to make bioplastics, such as corn starch.", options:["Crude oil","A concept unrelated to bioplastics","Corn starch","Coal"], answer:2},
     {q:"Why might bioplastics be considered a more environmentally friendly option than some traditional plastics?", options:["This concept has no connection to materials science","They can be made from renewable resources and may break down more easily in some cases","Bioplastics have no environmental benefit compared to traditional plastics","Traditional plastics are always more sustainable than bioplastics"], answer:1},
     {q:"Why might researchers continue working to improve bioplastic technology?", options:["This concept has no relevance to science","Bioplastics never have any limitations to address","Bioplastic technology has already been perfected with no room for improvement","Some bioplastics still face challenges, like cost or how well they break down in different environments"], answer:3}
